.TH WORK2MD-CONFIG 1 "March 2026" "work2md 0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
work2md-config \- manage shared work2md credentials and validation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B work2md-config
.I init
.br
.B work2md-config
.I show
.br
.B work2md-config
.I validate
.br
.B work2md-config
.I doctor
.br
.B work2md-config
.I path
.br
.B work2md-config
.RB [ --log-format " text|json ]"
.I jira
.BR init " | " show " | " validate " | " doctor
.br
.B work2md-config
.I jira
.B set
.I base|email|token|token-expiry|token-backend VALUE
.br
.B work2md-config
.RB [ --log-format " text|json ]"
.I confluence
.BR init " | " show " | " validate " | " doctor
.br
.B work2md-config
.I confluence
.B set
.I base|email|token|token-expiry|token-backend VALUE
.br
.B work2md-config
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B work2md-config
manages the shared configuration used by
.BR jira2md (1)
and
.BR confluence2md (1).
The default configuration file is
.IR ~/.config/work2md/config .
Its containing directory is kept at mode 700 and the config file at mode 600.
Existing configs with broader permissions are tightened automatically before
they are read or written.
Per-service token storage can be configured as either
.B config
or
.B keyring
using the
.B token-backend
setting.
The
.B keyring
backend uses the supported Linux keyring provider through
.B secret-tool
from the
.B libsecret-tools
package.
API tokens may also be supplied through the
.B WORK2MD_JIRA_TOKEN
and
.B WORK2MD_CONFLUENCE_TOKEN
environment variables so they do not need to be stored in the config file.
When set, those variables override the stored tokens at runtime and provide the
recommended fallback when no supported keyring backend is available.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Interactively initialize both Jira and Confluence settings.
.TP
.B show
Print the current configuration with secrets masked.
.TP
.B validate
Validate the configured values and perform live API checks when possible.
.TP
.B doctor
Run a more detailed diagnostic that checks base URLs, auth fields, keyring
availability, token expiry, and a short authenticated API probe.
.TP
.B path
Print the path to the active configuration file.
.TP
.BI "jira init, jira show, jira validate, jira doctor"
Manage or inspect only the Jira configuration.
.TP
.BI "jira set " "base|email|token|token-expiry|token-backend VALUE"
Set one Jira configuration field.
.TP
.BI "confluence init, confluence show, confluence validate, confluence doctor"
Manage or inspect only the Confluence configuration.
.TP
.BI "confluence set " "base|email|token|token-expiry|token-backend VALUE"
Set one Confluence configuration field.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show usage information.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Show the installed version.
.TP
.BI "\-\-log-format " "text|json"
Select plain text or JSON formatted log output on stderr.
